description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;WORCESTERSHIRE OLDER ADULT COMMUNITY MENTAL HEALTH SERVICE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;DUTY AND TRIAGE TEAM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;BASED AT KINGS COURT 2, WORCESTER &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;COMMUNITY MENTAL HEALTH NURSE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;BAND 6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;37.5 HOURS PER WEEK &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Worcestershire is a diverse county, boasting great transport networks to Birmingham and the rest of the UK, picturesque countryside and a rich history. Worcester city is voted the happiest city to live in and ranks in the top 3 for safety and friendliness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Worcestershire Health and Care Trust is an innovative and creative place to work.  Care and support of patients, their families and staff are at the heart of the organisation’s values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This new team started successfully in April 2020 have an opportunity for a full time mental health nurse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Team work predominately with people aged over 65 who have complex mental health problems; the team covers all of Worcestershire.  The team consists of Nurses, an Occupational Therapist, admin, all supported by a team manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post involves working as a cohesive team to manage and triage the incoming referrals to the service, either signposting to other agencies or if appropriate assigning them to a community mental health team for assessment and treatment.  The post also involved visiting patients that you have identified as urgent to complete an initial assessment and in some cases provide treatment in the short term.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have experience with the patient group and community work, with a sound knowledge of risk assessment; you will be offered 1-1 supervision and ongoing support.  You will enjoy working in a close knit team and will need to respond to incoming work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The 37.5 hours are to be worked over Monday to Friday 9.00am to 5.00pm, although the team is flexible and supports work-life balance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries to Catharine Jones Team Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;All staff whatever their role, level or responsibility will be encouraged and supported to do their job well and to improve their job.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Making Every Day Better for patients, staff, service users and carers is the responsibility of all of us and we want to embed a culture within the organisation that encourages and supports the drive to improve what we do.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
